    {
      "round": 0,
      "round_explanation": "Round 0 is the exploratory phase. No one yet knows others’ private valuations, so proposers are likely to test conservative, mildly generous terms to avoid universal rejection while still capturing clear surplus. Buffalo, with strong cognitive reflection, will likely start with a small, safe trade that improves her position in expected value terms while probing interest in exchanging her low-value red for green or blue. Bear, who values both red and blue highly, will probably test whether others are willing to give up red (or possibly blue) in exchange for green, aiming for a strongly positive expected surplus while not appearing exploitative. Goose, being logical and inequality-tolerant, is likely to respond by accepting any clearly positive gains and may propose trades that move from colors she values least (red/blue) into green, or modest swaps intended to elicit information about others’ priorities.",
